Immunohistochemical studies in a hydroptic fetus with pulmonary lymphangiectasia and trisomy 21. This case report presents a hydroptic trisomy 21 fetus affected by lymphatic dysplasia with no other malformations. Our studies using CD31, CD34, smooth muscle actin, desmin, and D2-40 antibodies immunohistochemistry confirm the diagnosis of severe pulmonary lymphangiectasia associated with lymphangiectasia ih the mediastinum and small bowel.